The paper discusses digital memcomputing machines (DMMs) which are designed to solve combinatorial optimization problems. This topic falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the use of a supersymmetric theory of dynamics, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the mapping of logic problems into dynamical systems, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Finally, the paper discusses the number of elementary instantons needed to reach the solution, which falls under the category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
